UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2070
1 AN ACT relating to preschool education programs.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 Section 1. KRS 157.320 is amended to read as follows:
4 As used in KRS 157.310 to 157.440, unless the context otherwise requires:
5 (1) "Administrative regulations of the Kentucky Board of Education" means those
6 regulations which the Kentucky Board of Education may adopt upon the
7 recommendation and with the advice of the commissioner of education. The
8 commissioner of education shall recommend administrative regulations necessary
9 for carrying out the purposes of KRS 157.310 to 157.440;
10 (2) "Average daily attendance" means the aggregate days attended by pupils in a public
11 school, adjusted for weather-related low attendance days if applicable, divided by
12 the actual number of days the school is in session, after the five (5) days with the
13 lowest attendance have been deducted.
14 (a) Aggregate days shall include, in addition to the aggregate number of days
15 attended by a pupil who was suspended during a school year, the number of
16 days the pupil was suspended, not to exceed ten (10) days in total for the
17 school year; and
18 (b) Aggregate days shall include, in addition to the aggregate number of days
19 attended by a pupil who was expelled for behavioral problems, the number of
20 days the pupil was expelled up to a total of one hundred seventy-five (175)
21 days. This total may extend into the next school year and shall be counted in
22 the average daily attendance for the next year;
23 (3) "Base funding level" means a guaranteed amount of revenue per pupil to be
24 provided for each school district, to be used for regular operating and capital
25 expenditures;
26 (4) "Board" means the board of education of any county or independent school district;
27 (5) "District" means any school district as defined by law;
Page 1 of 12
XXXX 2/4/2026 6:36 PM Jacketed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2070
1 (6) "Elementary school" means a school consisting of the primary school program
2 through grade eight (8) as defined in KRS 158.030, or any appropriate combination
3 of grades within this range, as determined by the plan of organization for schools
4 authorized by the district board;
5 (7) "Eligible child" means for preschool education programs, a child who is:
6 (a) Four (4) years of age by August 1; or
7 (b) Three (3) or four (4) years of age with a disability in accordance with the
8 Individuals with Disabilities Education Act, 20 U.S.C. sec. 1400 et seq.
9 (8) "Experience" means employment as a teacher, other than as a substitute or nursery
10 school teacher, for a minimum of one hundred forty (140) days during a school year
11 in a public or nonpublic elementary or secondary school or college or university
12 that is approved by the public accrediting authority in the state in which the
13 teaching duties were performed. A teacher who is employed by a board for at least
14 one hundred forty (140) days of a school year and who performs teaching duties for
15 the equivalent of at least seventy (70) full school days during that school year,
16 regardless of the schedule on which those duties were performed, shall be credited
17 with one (1) year of experience. A teacher who is employed by a board for at least
18 one hundred forty (140) days during each of two (2) school years and who performs
19 teaching duties for the equivalent of at least seventy (70) full school days during
20 those years shall be credited with one (1) year of experience. No more than one (1)
21 year of experience shall be credited for the performance of teaching duties during a
22 single school year;
23 (9)[(8)] "Kindergarten full-time equivalent pupil in average daily attendance" means
24 each kindergarten pupil counted no more than one-half (1/2) day in the aggregate
25 days attended by kindergarten pupils in a public school divided by the actual
26 number of days school is in session after the five (5) days with the lowest
27 attendance have been deducted. Kindergarten is the entry level of the primary
Page 2 of 12
