UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2070
1 program and shall be provided no less than the equivalent of one-half (1/2) day, five
2 (5) days a week for a full school year for each kindergarten pupil;
3 (10)[(9)] "Middle school" means a school consisting of grades five (5) through eight (8)
4 or any appropriate combination of grades as determined by the plan of organization
5 for schools authorized by the district board;
6 (11)[(10)] "National board certification salary supplement" means an annual supplement
7 added for the life of the certificate to the base salary of a teacher who attains
8 national board certification;
9 (12)[(11)] "Percentage of attendance" means the aggregate days attended by pupils in a
10 public school for the school year divided by the aggregate days' membership of
11 pupils in a public school for the school year;
12 (13)[(12)] "Public school fund" means the fund created by KRS 157.330 for use in
13 financing education in public elementary and secondary schools;
14 (14)[(13)] "Secondary school" means a school consisting of grades seven (7) through
15 twelve (12), or any appropriate combination of grades within this range as
16 determined by the plan of organization for schools authorized by the district board.
17 When grades seven (7) through nine (9) or ten (10) are organized separately as a
18 junior high school, or grades ten (10) through twelve (12) are organized separately
19 as a senior high school and are conducted in separate school plant facilities, each
20 shall be considered a separate secondary school for the purposes of KRS 157.310 to
21 157.440;
22 (15)[(14)] "Single salary schedule" means a schedule adopted by a local board from
23 which all teachers are paid for one hundred eighty-five (185) days and is based on
24 training, experience, and such other factors as the Kentucky Board of Education
25 may approve and which does not discriminate between salaries paid elementary and
26 secondary teachers. If the budget bill contains a minimum statewide salary
27 schedule, no teacher shall be paid less than the amount specified in the biennial
Page 3 of 12
