UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2070
1 who ]
2 1. Is four (4) years of age [:
3 (a) By October 1, for any year prior to 2017; or
4 (b) ]by August 1; and
5 2. Resides in a household with an income at or below one hundred sixty
6 percent (160%) of the federal poverty level[, for 2017 or any year
7 thereafter].
8 All other four (4) year old children shall be served to the extent placements are
9 available.
10 (b) No later than July 1, 2034, each local school district shall ensure that a
11 developmentally appropriate half-day preschool education program is
12 provided for each eligible child as defined in Section 1 of this Act. Prior to
13 the 2034-2035 school year, each local school district may elect to ensure
14 that a developmentally appropriate half-day preschool education program is
15 provided for each eligible child as defined in Section 1 of this Act.
16 (2) The Kentucky Board of Education, upon the recommendation of the chief state
17 school officer, shall adopt administrative regulations establishing the guidelines for
18 the program. The program guidelines established shall be applicable to all
19 providers of preschool education programs and services pursuant to this section,
20 including teaming partners. The guidelines shall include:
21 (a) Enrollment eligibility criteria;
22 (b) Minimum class sizes and staff-to-child ratio;
23 (c) Standards for personnel;
24 (d) The minimum number of hours and days programs shall operate;
25 (e) Standards for curriculum that are aligned with Kentucky's Early Childhood
26 Standards;
27 (f) Standards for ensuring enrolled children are kindergarten ready;
Page 5 of 12
