UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2070
1 (g) Requirements for facilities, safety, health, and transportation;
2 (h) Processes for the collection and reporting of data necessary to implement
3 subsection (3) of this section;
4 (i) Guidance for local school districts providing preschool education programs
5 or services in collaboration with teaming partners; and
6 (j) Any other guidelines necessary to provide developmentally appropriate
7 preschool education programs or services or to implement the provisions of
8 this section.
9 (3) (a) The Kentucky Department of Education shall establish and maintain a
10 statewide unified data system for all preschool education program
11 providers.
12 (b) Providers shall collect and submit to the department on an annual basis
13 enrollment, quality, workforce, and student success data.
14 (c) By November 1 of each year, the department shall publish the data to a
15 public website designated for that purpose[Administrative regulations shall
16 establish eligibility criteria, program guidelines, and standards for personnel].
17 (4)[(2)] "Developmentally appropriate preschool program" means a program which
18 focuses on the physical, intellectual, social, and emotional development of young
19 children. The preschool program shall help children with their interpersonal and
20 socialization skills.
21 (5)[(3)] Funds appropriated by the General Assembly for the preschool education
22 programs shall be granted to local school districts according to a grant allotment
23 system approved by the Kentucky Board of Education. [Children who are at risk
24 shall be identified based on the Federal School Lunch Program eligibility criteria
25 for free lunch. ]Appropriations shall be separate from all other funds appropriated
26 to the Department of Education and shall be administered in accordance with
27 applicable federal and state statutes and administrative regulations. Eligible local
