1 (a) A description of the process conducted by the district to ensure that the
2 parents or guardians of all eligible participants have been made aware of the
3 program and of their right to participate;
4 (b) A description of the planned educational programming and related services;
5 (c) The estimated number of children participating in the program;
6 (d) Strategies for involving children with disabilities;
7 (e) Estimated ratio of staff to children with the maximum being one (1) adult for
8 each ten (10) children;
9 (f) The estimated percentage of children participating in the program who are at
10 risk[ of educational failure];
11 (g) Information on the training and qualifications of program staff and
12 documentation that the staff meet required standards;
13 (h) A budget and per-child expenditure estimate;
14 (i) A plan to facilitate active parental involvement in the preschool program,
15 including provisions for complementary parent education when appropriate;
16 (j) Facilities and equipment which are appropriate for young children;
17 (k) The days of the week and hours of a day during which the program shall
18 operate;
19 (l) A plan for coordinating the program with existing medical and social services,
20 including a child development and health screening component;
21 (m) Assurances that participants shall receive breakfast or lunch;
22 (n) Program sites which meet state and local licensure requirements;
23 (o) A plan for coordinating program philosophy and activities with the local
24 district's primary school program;
25 (p) An evaluation component; and
26 (q) Certification from the local Head Start director that the Head Start program is
27 fully utilized pursuant to subsection (7)[(4)] of this section.
